Thank you for using PyAcademy, your interactive app for learning Python programming.
Your privacy is very important to us, and we are committed to keeping your personal information safe while providing an effective and enjoyable learning experience.

🧩 Data Collection

PyAcademy does not collect any personal data such as your name, email address, or photos.

However, basic technical data (like IP address, device type, operating system version, and timestamps) may be collected automatically for:

Analytics and performance improvement

Security monitoring

App functionality and stability

This data is non-identifiable and is used solely to enhance the app experience.

🧱 Local Storage

All your progress, lessons, and learning preferences are stored locally on your device.
We do not upload, share, or back up any of your study data to remote servers.

💰 Advertisements

PyAcademy uses Google AdMob to display advertisements.

AdMob may use cookies or mobile identifiers to:

Show relevant ads

Measure ad performance

Prevent fraud and abuse

You can learn more about Google’s data practices here:
🔗 https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads

🍪 Cookies and Similar Technologies

Cookies or similar technologies may be used to:

Save app settings (dark/light mode)

Remember your language preferences

Improve app performance

You can manage or disable cookies at any time through your device settings.

🔔 Notifications

PyAcademy may send notifications or study reminders to help you stay consistent in your learning journey.
You may disable notifications from your device settings at any time.

🔐 Data Security

All data transmitted through the app (including ad requests) is encrypted in transit.
While we use reasonable means to ensure your privacy, no internet transmission can be guaranteed 100% secure.

🤝 Data Sharing

We do not share any user data with third parties except as necessary for integrated services such as Google AdMob.
Each third-party service follows its own privacy policy regarding data use.

🧹 Data Deletion

If you wish to delete any data collected through third-party services (such as AdMob), you may send a deletion request to the contact email below.
We will process your request promptly and delete any available data as soon as possible.

🔗 Links to Third-Party Sites

PyAcademy may include educational links or references to external websites.
We are not responsible for the content or privacy practices of these third-party sites.

🔄 Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time.
All updates will be posted here with a revised “Last Updated” date.
We encourage you to review this page regularly to stay informed about how we protect your data.

